[1
Date: Wed 7 Feb 2001 16:34:33 -0500
From: Rashid A. Chotani <Rashid.Chotani@jhuapl.edu>
Source: Reuters Report, Wed 7 Feb 2001 3:53PM ET [edited

Ebola Fever Ruled Out
---------------------
TORONTO: A woman lying sick in a Canadian hospital after arriving from [the
Democratic Republic of Congo does not have the deadly Ebola virus, but
could have another type of tropical viral hemorrhagic fever, government
health officials said on Wednesday. "Ebola [fever has been ruled out from
Health Canada's perspective," Dr Douglas MacPherson, a government
infectious disease specialist, told a news conference. "There are still
other viral hemorrhagic tropical fevers under consideration," he added.
The woman, who flew to Toronto from the Democratic Republic of Congo via
New York on Saturday, was admitted to a hospital in Hamilton, Ontario, on
Sunday and placed in quarantine. Doctors said on Wednesday they expect to
receive test results from a special laboratory in Winnipeg, Manitoba.
Health officials said they are still being "super cautious" when dealing
with the woman, and continue to maintain close surveillance on people who
came in close contact with her, including 2 of her personal contacts and 10
hospital workers.
--
RA Chotani, MD, MPH
Johns Hopkins University
<Rashid.Chotani@jhuapl.edu>
[This first report does not make clear the basis for ruling out a diagnosis
of Ebola fever. - Mod.CP
